    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Not included into <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/></bibl>;
                    mention and photograph in <bibl><ptr target="#menozzi-divalerio-tamburrino2017"/>, pp. <citedRange>83-84</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/> <citedRange>67.1494</citedRange></bibl>;
                epigraphic publication <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2020c"/>, p. <citedRange>321</citedRange>, n. 11 and fig. 12</bibl>.</p>
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="..."><name nymRef="#Ἄριστις">Ἄριστις</name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="..."><name nymRef="#Εὐρυκράτης" type="patronymic"/>Εὐρυκράτευς</persName>
                </ab>
            </div>
            
            <div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div>
            
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Arisitis fils d'Eurykratès.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aristis son of Eurykrates.</p>
		    </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>Aristis figlio di Eurykrates.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Aristis is a very common name in Cyrenaica. The father's name is up to now not attested in the region, although its two components are common here.</p>
                <p/>
                <p/>
            </div>
        </body>
